title: Vincent Banet
text:
Vincent Banet is a French <a href="rugby%20league">rugby league</a> footballer who represented <a href="France%20national%20rugby%20league%20team">France</a> at the <a href="1995%20Rugby%20League%20World%20Cup">1995 World Cup</a>.
Playing career.
From the <a href="XIII%20Catalan">Catalan club</a>, Banet played for the France under-18's in a 1993 match against their Great Britain counterparts.
He was later signed by <a href="Workington%20Town">Workington Town</a>, and made his début in October 1994.
He returned to France after the season, joining the <a href="Limoux%20Grizzlies">Limoux club</a>. In 1995 he made his début for <a href="France%20national%20rugby%20league%20team">France</a>, coming off the bench in one match at the <a href="1995%20Rugby%20League%20World%20Cup">1995 World Cup</a>.
He played in two more matches for France, against <a href="South%20Africa%20national%20rugby%20league%20team">South Africa</a> in 1997 and <a href="Scotland%20national%20rugby%20league%20team">Scotland</a> in 1998.
In 2002 he played for the <a href="AS%20Carcassonne">Carcassonne Canaries</a>.
